---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Navbar from "../../components/Navbar.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout title="First Blog Post | asim shirinov">
    <Navbar />

    <main
        class="w-full flex justify-center py-20 md:py-24 px-6 flex-grow flex-1"
    >
        <article class="max-w-[820px] w-full flex flex-col gap-6 pt-4">
            <a
                href="/#blog"
                class="text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors text-sm font-medium flex items-center gap-1.5 w-fit mb-2"
            >
                <svg
                    xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                    width="16"
                    height="16"
                    viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                    fill="none"
                    stroke="currentColor"
                    stroke-width="2"
                    stroke-linecap="round"
                    stroke-linejoin="round"
                    ><path d="m15 18-6-6 6-6"></path>
                </svg>
                Back to home
            </a>

            <!-- Header -->
            <header class="flex flex-col gap-3 mb-4">
                <h1
                    class="text-text-primary text-3xl md:text-4xl font-[var(--font-weight-bold)] tracking-tight"
                >
                    First Blog Post
                </h1>
                <div
                    class="text-text-secondary font-[var(--font-weight-medium)] text-[14px] flex items-center gap-2"
                >
                    <time datetime="2026-02-28">February 28, 2026</time>
                    <span>•</span>
                    <span>About 5 min read</span>
                </div>
            </header>

            <!-- Content -->
            <div
                class="prose text-[1.25em] prose-invert prose-p:text-text-primary prose-p:leading-relaxed prose-headings:text-text-primary prose-a:text-white hover:prose-a:text-gray-300 prose-strong:text-white max-w-none"
            >
                <p>
                    Have you ever seen someone so good at what they do that you
                    think "Damn, one day I want to be as good as this guy"?
                    <br />
                    <br />
                </p>

                <p>
                    Everything started with <a
                        href="https://scratch.mit.edu/"
                        target="_blank"
                        rel="noopener noreferrer">Scratch</a
                    >. I have been making games and small coding projects which
                    helped me develop problem solving skills since I was 12. One
                    day, while browsing YouTube I came across someone who was
                    teaching competitive programming in my native language,
                    Abutalib-Barish Namazov. There were four videos, each video
                    lasting around three hours. After watching one of the videos
                    I was impressed by how good he was and how well he explained
                    things.
                    <br />
                    <br />
                </p>

                <p>
                    In December 2025, I saw his blog and read some of his blog
                    posts which were pretty interesting and fun to read. I sent
                    him an email and asked for advice, because he was an
                    inspiring and intelligent person for me and I wanted some
                    guidance in my field about what to do, and he gave me some
                    good advice. One of the pieces of advice is that I should
                    learn how to write well. I guess he is trying to say that I
                    should be able to write and communicate well, which are
                    pretty important skills.
                    <br />
                    <br />
                </p>

                <p>
                    So I know some really smart people majoring in computer
                    science at top universities and realized that they have
                    their own websites and blogs. They use them to share what
                    they do and document their progress. Why can't I? I could
                    learn the technical stuff like hosting, domains, and website
                    deployment, and at the same time I could share my thoughts
                    and improve myself through writing.
                    <br />
                    <br />
                </p>

                <p>
                    In the rest of this blog, I will write about my daily life,
                    technology, the things I am learning, and whatever else
                    genuinely interests me.
                    <br />
                    <br />
                </p>

                <p>Thank you so much for reading.</p>
            </div>
        </article>
    </main>

    <Footer />
</Layout>
